      <processinfo id="aspace_87b7e7a74bb66be1ef51ce619b957cde">
         <head>Processing Information</head>
         <p>Yale University records are arranged and described at the accession level by the creating office. The University Archives creates collection level descriptive records, but typically does no further arrangement and description at the accession level.</p>  
      </processinfo>
      <bioghist id="aspace_41004e6cba6c252d36867bfe6d798879">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Organized by the African American house (now Afro-American Cultural Center) in the 1970s, the Black Tie Society was a program that promoted interaction between African American Studies faculty and students at Yale.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_8fb02548d1fc4ea70f61e01525efb4d0">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The materials consist of a directory, newsletter, and correspondence.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement id="aspace_07b224884a14191b83f0cfcc55156bbf">
